## Style Review Checklist

Before committing any style changes, verify:

1. ✅ Only dark mode classes/utilities used
2. ✅ All custom utilities/components from `index.css`
3. ✅ No use of `!important`
4. ✅ All headings, buttons, cards, and inputs consistent with reference
5. ✅ All new styles documented in StyleDemo
6. ✅ Style cascade and specificity correct
7. ✅ UI visually consistent across all pages and modals
8. ✅ Overlay action buttons have proper padding
9. ✅ Anchor sections use `section-anchor` class

## File Organization

### CSS Files
- `index.css` - Main stylesheet with custom utilities
- Component-specific styles should be in component files
- Use CSS modules or styled-components for complex styling

### Image Assets
- `public/images/logo.png` - Main logo
- `public/images/sml_whitelogo.png` - White logo variant
- `public/images/sml_darklogo.png` - Dark logo variant

## Common Patterns to Avoid

- ❌ Light mode classes (`bg-white`, `text-black`)
- ❌ `!important` declarations
- ❌ Inline styles (except for demo purposes)
- ❌ Hardcoded colors (use design system colors)
- ❌ Inconsistent spacing or typography
- ❌ Missing responsive considerations

## Adding New Styles

1. Add new utilities to `index.css`
2. Document in StyleDemo component
3. Follow existing naming conventions
4. Test across different screen sizes
5. Ensure dark mode compatibility
6. Update this style guide if needed